page.title: 09A FRISKNEY LADY
page.content:
Woke up at 6.45 a.m. switched on the radio and teasmade and enjoyed a cup of tea while listening to the news. Ater breakfast a phone call confirmed the time I would collect a friend for a doctor's appointment in Wainfleet. Just as I was leaving another friend rang to see if I could go with her to Boston. This was impossible as I have to play the organ for a funeral at 11 a.m. Fortunately my "meals on wheels" rota does not occur this Thursday. Remember that tomorrow the Library Van calls and to decide on the food for the weekend for my Canadian visitors. Prepare guest room after dinner. Went to the Vicarage for choir practice at 6.30 followed by 7 o'clock Communion Bible Study and Discussion Group and then to bed.
Mrs. P. Robinson
